<body><div class=WordSection1>
<div class="brand">📚 ENGLISH CODING · 영어코딩</div>
<h1>🏃 RB001 Week 3 — English Worksheet (Beginner)</h1>
<p><strong>Topic:</strong> Functions &amp; Events — the Lava Floor · <strong>Course:</strong> Obby Architect · <strong>Level:</strong> Beginner · <strong>Time:</strong> about 30 minutes</p>
<p>This week you learned <strong>functions</strong> and the <strong>Touched event</strong>. <code>lava.Touched:Connect(onTouch)</code> tells Roblox: "when something touches the lava, run this function."</p>
<hr />
<h2>1 · Predict 🔮</h2>
<p>Read the script. Before you run anything, circle or write your answer.</p>
<pre><code class="language-lua">local lava = script.Parent

local function onTouch(otherPart)
    print(&quot;Something touched the lava!&quot;)
end

lava.Touched:Connect(onTouch)
</code></pre>
<p><strong>The game starts but nothing has touched the lava yet. Does the message print? Circle one:</strong> yes · no</p>
<p><strong>Why?</strong></p>
<p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p>

<pre><code class="language-lua">local lava = script.Parent

local function onTouch(otherPart)
    local humanoid = otherPart.Parent:FindFirstChildWhichIsA(&quot;Humanoid&quot;)
    if humanoid then
        humanoid.Health = 0
    end
end

lava.Touched:Connect(onTouch)
</code></pre>
<p><strong>A player steps on the lava. Does their health go to 0? Circle one:</strong> yes · no</p>
<p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p>

<hr />
<h2>2 · Find the Difference 🐛</h2>
<p>Each pair shows clean code first, then a broken version of the same idea. Circle what's different and write one short sentence about the bug.</p>
<p><strong>Pair A</strong> — The lava should print a message when touched. One line is missing in the buggy version.</p>
<pre><code class="language-lua">-- clean
local lava = script.Parent

local function onTouch(otherPart)
    print(&quot;Hot!&quot;)
end

lava.Touched:Connect(onTouch)
</code></pre>
<pre><code class="language-lua">-- buggy
local lava = script.Parent

local function onTouch(otherPart)
    print(&quot;Hot!&quot;)
end
</code></pre>
<p><strong>What is wrong? Why does the buggy function never run?</strong></p>
<p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p>

<p><strong>Pair B</strong> — The lava should kill players only. The buggy version forgets the safety check.</p>
<pre><code class="language-lua">-- clean
local function onTouch(otherPart)
    local humanoid = otherPart.Parent:FindFirstChildWhichIsA(&quot;Humanoid&quot;)
    if humanoid then
        humanoid.Health = 0
    end
end
</code></pre>
<pre><code class="language-lua">-- buggy
local function onTouch(otherPart)
    local humanoid = otherPart.Parent:FindFirstChildWhichIsA(&quot;Humanoid&quot;)
    humanoid.Health = 0
end
</code></pre>
<p><strong>What is wrong?</strong></p>
<p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p>

<hr />
<h2>3 · Fill the Gap ✏️</h2>
<p>The script should run the function when the lava is touched. One word is missing. Fill it in using the word bank.</p>
<pre><code class="language-lua">lava.Touched:____(onTouch)
</code></pre>
<p><strong>Word bank:</strong> <code>Connect</code> · <code>print</code> · <code>local</code></p>
<p><strong>Write the missing word:</strong></p>
<p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p>

<p>The function needs its closing word. One word is missing.</p>
<pre><code class="language-lua">local function onTouch(otherPart)
    print(&quot;Hot!&quot;)
____
</code></pre>
<p><strong>Word bank:</strong> <code>end</code> · <code>local</code> · <code>true</code></p>
<p><strong>Write the missing word:</strong></p>
<p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p>

<hr />
<h2>4 · Tell Me What You Built 📸</h2>
<p>Now switch to your own obby in Roblox Studio. Build a lava floor section with a kill brick — touch the lava and your character's health drops to 0. When you finish, come back here.</p>
<p>Send a photo or video of your lava section, then explain what you did. Use these sentence starters — write 2 or 3 sentences.</p>
<blockquote>
<p>My function runs when …</p>
<p>The lava kills the player by …</p>
<p>One tricky moment was when …</p>
</blockquote>
<p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p>

<hr />
<h2>5 · Record Your Walkthrough 🎥</h2>
<p>Take a video on your phone (or a parent's phone) while a player runs your lava section. Talk like you are teaching a friend. Try to use these words: <strong>function</strong>, <strong>event</strong>, <strong>Touched</strong>, <strong>Connect</strong>.</p>
<blockquote>
<ol>
<li>Run the game and step on the lava.</li>
<li>Read your <code>lava.Touched:Connect(onTouch)</code> line out loud.</li>
<li>Say in your own words what an <strong>event</strong> is.</li>
</ol>
</blockquote>
<p><strong>Write what you will say in your video.</strong> You can read from it while filming.</p>
<p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p>

<hr />
<h3>Submit ✅</h3>
<p>Send this worksheet + your walkthrough video to teacher on KakaoTalk.</p>
<div class="footer">영어코딩 · <b>english-coding.co.uk</b></div>
</div></body></html>
